Adding PHPMailer 7.01
Checking Ruleset Main & Feature Branch Protection."

Summary Checklist for Future Workflows
git fetch (Check for updates)
git pull --rebase (Sync locally)
Make your changes.
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git pull --rebase (Sync again before pushing, just in case)
git push
By following this routine, you'll rarely encounter the "non-fast-forward" error again! 🚀

What Happens Now?
Ruleset name:  "Main & Feature Branch Protection."
Once this ruleset is active:
Direct Pushes Blocked: If you try git push directly to that branch, GitHub will reject it with a message saying "Pushes to this branch are not permitted."
Force Pushes Blocked: If you try git push --force, it will be blocked immediately.
Workflow Change: You will now have to:
Create a new branch (e.g., feature/my-fix).
Push that new branch.
Open a Pull Request to merge it into civara_phpmailer_proton_secure_bundle.zip.
Merge the PR via the GitHub UI.
Note: This rule applies to all branches that that start with "Civara_"


 
